MALACAÑANG Manila

PROCLAMATION NO. 261

AMENDING PROCLAMATION NO. 297 DATED DECEMBER 15, 1951 WHICH RESERVED CERTAIN PARCELS OF LAND OF THE PRIVATE DOMAIN OF THE GOVERNMENT LOCATED IN MA-A DAVAO CITY FOR RADIO STATION SITE PURPOSES UNDER THE ADMINISTRATION OF THE DIRECTOR OF TELECOMMUNICATIONS BY EXCLUDING CERTAIN PORTION OF THE LAND EMBRACED THEREIN AND DECLARING THE SAME OPEN FOR DISPOSITION IN FAVOR OF THE ACTUAL OCCUPANTS

Upon the recommendation of the Secretary of Environment and Natural Resources and by virtue of the powers vested in me by law, I, GLORIA MACAPAGAL-ARROYO , President of the Philippines, do hereby amend Proclamation No. 297 dated December 15, 1951 which reserved certain parcels of land of the private domain of the government located in Ma-a, Davao City for radio station site purposes under the administration of the Director of Telecommunications by excluding certain portion of the land embraced therein identified as Lot no. 14-B, Psd-11-067841 containing an area of Eighty Nine Thousand Eight Hundred Thirteen (89,813) square meters located in Ma-a, Davao City and declaring the same open for disposition in favor of the actual occupants in accordance with the provisions of Republic Act No. 477 dated June 9, 1950, as implemented by Joint Circular No. 1 dated September 30, 1989, of the Departments of Environment and Natural Resources, Public Works and Highways and Budget and Management; and retain the other portion identified as Lot No. 14-A, Psd-11-067841, containing an area of Twenty Seven Thousand Five Hundred Twenty (27,520) square meters , under the administration of the Telecommunications Office, subject to private rights, if any there be and whatever understanding that may hereto be agreed upon between the Department of Transportation and Communication and the City Government of Davao regarding the area being utilized by the Davao City Jail, which parcels of land are more particularly described as follows:

